Ōtepoti Youth Vision

The Ōtepoti Youth Vision was officially launched at Toitū Settlers Museum on 16 May 2019. Young people and representatives from organisations across the city joined together to celebrate the development of the Vision, and its future.

ABOUT

The Dunedin Youth Council is a group of 14 high school students working under the wider Dunedin City Council to advocate for youth in local government .

We achieve this by running events, distributing information, and the most important thing of all, working with youth!
